-- Radian posts profit on fewer home loan defaults
-- By Neha Dimri in Bangalore
-- Tue May 06, 2014 04:37PM EDT
-- None



May 6 (Reuters) - Radian Group Inc <RDN.N>, the biggest U.S. private mortgage insurer, reported a quarterly profit compared with a loss a year earlier as fewer homeowners defaulted on their loans.

The company's net income was $202.8 million, or 94 cents per share, for the first quarter ended March 31, compared with a loss of $187.5 million, or $1.30 per share, a year earlier. [ID:nBw1Lg4qa]